headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid GEV and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: GE Vernova’s 28.4% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 22.5%, and its stock price has climbed to $802.45 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
